place.name: GATELEY
place.gazetteerText: GATELY, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; on an affluent of the river Wensum, 2 miles S of Ryburgh r. station, and 4¼ SSE of Fakenham. Post town, Ryburgh, under Fakenham. Acres, 1, 490. Real property, £1, 706. Pop., 134. Houses, 28. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage, annexed to the rectory of Brisley, in the diocese of Norwich. The church was reported in 1859 as not good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
